article.headline: Yale 79, N.J. Tech 48
article.story: NEW HAVEN, Conn. -- Alex Zampier scored 15 points and 11 Yale players got on the score sheet in a 79-48 rout of New Jersey Institute of Technology on Saturday. Porter Braswell added 14 points, Michael Sands 11 and Reggie Willhite 10 for the Bulldogs (6-11). Braswell hit four of his five 3-point attempts for the Bulldogs, who finished 9-for-21 from beyond the arc (42.9 percent). The Highlanders were just 5 of 17 from long range (29.4 percent). Yale also was 85.7 percent from the free throw line (18-for-21) compared to a 65 percent mark (13-for-20) for NJIT. The Bulldogs led by nine points at halftime and sealed it on 28-8 run to open the second half. Chris Flores scored 18 points and Jheryl Wilson added 16 for the Highlanders (5-11), who have dropped three in a row. Yale has won two straight since dropping five consecutive games.
